'''''Star Wars Tales''''' (occasionally styled as '''''Star Wars: Tales''''') is a quasi-canonical<ref name="TERC">''[[The Essential Reader's Companion]]''</ref> [[Star Wars Legends|Legends]] [[Star Wars comic books|comic book]] anthology series from [[Dark Horse Comics]]. It had a twenty-four issue run and was published quarterly, beginning in [[1999]] and concluding in [[2005]]. Each issue features several short stories from various creators that are set in multiple eras of ''[[Star Wars]]'' storytelling. ''Star Wars Tales'' was collected in six paperback volumes that each contain four issues.

==Development==
The [[Free Comic Book Day]] issue [[Free Comic Book Day 2002 Special|''Star Wars: Tales—A Jedi's Weapon'']] was published in [[May]] [[2002]]. It is comprised of the story "[[A Jedi's Weapon]],"<ref name="Jedi's Weapon">[[Free Comic Book Day 2002 Special]]</ref> which was later featured in [[Star Wars Tales 12|''Star Wars Tales'' 12]].<ref name="Tales 12">[[Star Wars Tales 12|''Star Wars Tales'' 12]]</ref>

==Continuity==
Some of the stories featured in ''Star Wars Tales'' are non-continuity. The success of the series ultimately led to ''[[Star Wars Infinities]]'', a group of [[Star Wars comic books|comic book]] miniseries that tell alternate-history versions of the ''[[Star Wars]]'' [[original trilogy]].<ref name="Comics Companion">''[[Star Wars: The Comics Companion]]''</ref>

